  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0db1\u0dca \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9d\u0ddd\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Those involved in the tourism business are protesting",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A group of people engaged in agitation in front of the Bentota tourist resort today (22nd) claiming that they will not be given relief from the state and private banks in the tourism business.",
        "The agitators said that they are now in an unspeakable difficulty as they have to pay the concessions given to them by the banks along with the interest at the same time as the corona virus in the country.",
        "They said that with the current situation of the country, at a time when the tourism business has gone down to zero, they cannot pay the installments and interest money demanded by the banks, so now they have to eat or sell their two kidneys for money.",
        "The agitators say that if the relevant authorities do not take any action in this regard, they can take care of the Adona of Bentota Tourism tomorrow."
      ],
